      "writtenOn": "2020-11-19T17:22:40Z",
      "side": 0,
      "message": "We can\u0027t make any edits to the builtin structures at all if we\u0027re currently working on a Program, because that Program\u0027s pool will be active, and any IRNodes we create will be associated with that Program (and will leak/dissipate when that Pool goes away).\n\nSo, for \"the inliner is either operating on ALL builtin code, or NO builtin code\", this sounds fine, as long as when it\u0027s operating on ALL builtin code, it\u0027s not inside of convertProgram.",
